               <provenance>According to Additio 1, the owners are
                        ʾabuna Walda Madḫǝn, Ṣǝge ʾAragāwi, Gabra
                     Māryām, ʾAmata Māryām and others. Their names are written (in strong amaranth)
                     in the supplication formulas throughout the text: ʾabuna Walda Madḫǝn (e.g., 4va,
                     8vb, 11ra, 14ra, 15ra, 18vb, 20rb, 23ra, 25va, 36rb, 55vb, 60vb, 70ra, 83rb),
                     ʾAmata Māryām (e.g., 6vb, 13vb, 15ra, 19vb, 23ra,
                     25va, 32rb, 45ra, 60vb, 83rb), ʾAmata Gabrǝʾel (19rb, 21va), Ṣǝge ʾAragāwi (e.g., 21va, 26vb, 42vb, 54va, 65va,
                     77vb), Walatta Māryām (25va, 40va), Walatta
                     Gabrǝʾel (25va), Gabra Ḥǝywat (31vb, 41rb, 47ra, 50va, 55vb), Gabra Māryām (e.g.,
                        45ra, 48rb, 54rb, 71ra). 
 The ownership
                     note and the names in the supplication formulas are written in the same crude
                     secondary hand.
 The purchase note (Additio 2) mentiones priest Walda
                     Gabrǝʾel as the buyer and and ʾalaqā Gabra
                     ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer as the seller.</provenance></history>
